'''Strontium 90''' is a [[radioactive decay|radioactive]] [[isotope]] of [[strontium]]. It has a [[half life]] of roughly 29 years. Strontium 90 and Strontium 89 have medical applications. They are used for [[radioation therapy]],  in the treatment of certain [[bone cancer]]s. Because its application generates a lot of heat it is sometimes used instead of [[Plutonium]] in [[nuclear energy|nuclear power plant]]s. 


